cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.SY

The paper discusses the application of Independent Components Analysis (ICA) in machine learning and theoretical neuroscience, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on degeneracy control mechanisms in overcomplete ICA, which involves optimization and control theory, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well. The task of estimating an overcomplete basis on natural images suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves theoretical analysis, which could place it under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes novel approaches for degeneracy control, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
